IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROMOTE AND DEVELOP THE ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE PROGRAM IN THE STATE OF ILLINOIS; AND TO FURTHER THE GENERAL WELFARE AND TO PROTECT THE INTEREST OF ASSOCIATION MEMBERS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROMOTE AND DEVELOP THE ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE PROGRAM IN THE STATE OF ILLINOIS; AND TO FURTHER THE GENERAL WELFARE AND TO PROTECT THE INTERESTS OF ASSOCIATION MEMBERS.
IRS990.Desc: THE ASSOCIATION OF ILLINOIS ELECTRIC COOPERATIVES IS A MEMBER-OWNED ASSOCIATION THAT CONSISTS OF 30 MEMBER-COOPERATIVES. INFORMATION PUBLICATIONS IS ONE OF THE SERVICE PROGRAMS OFFERED BY THE ASSOCIATION THROUGH A MONTHLY PUBLICATION CONTAINING INFORMATION TO THE MEMBERSHIP WITH NEWS CONCERNING ELECTRIC BUSINESS AND THE RURAL ELECTRIFICATION PROGRAM.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE ASSOCIATION OF ILLINOIS ELECTRIC COOPERATIVES ALSO OFFERS EDUCATION PROGRAMS THAT PROVIDE RESOURCES FOR TRAINING OF INDIVIDUALS CONCERNING THE MANAGEMENT AND OPERATIONS OF CONSUMER-OWNED UTILITIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: THE ASSOCIATION OF ILLINOIS ELECTRIC COOPERATIVES OFFERS SAFETY PROGRAMS THAT PROVIDE RESOURCES FOR TRAINING IN SAFETY TECHNIQUES FOR ELECTRICAL DISTRIBUTION COOPERATIVES AND CIVIC ORGANIZATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AN EVALUATION OF WHETHER OR NOT IT HAS ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS IS DETERMINED ON AN ANNUAL BASIS BY THE ASSOCIATION. WHILE THE ASSOCIATION BELIEVES IT HAS ADEQUATELY PROVIDED FOR ALL TAX POSITIONS, AMOUNTS ASSERTED BY TAXING AUTHORITIES COULD BE DIFFERENT THAN THE POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE ASSOCIATION. THE ASSOCIATION RECOGNIZES ANY INTEREST AND PENALTIES ASSESSED BY TAXING AUTHORITIES IN INCOME TAX EXPENSE AND, WITH FEW EXCEPTIONS, IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS BY TAX AUTHORITIES FOR YEARS BEFORE 2019.
THE ASSOCIATION OF ILLINOIS ELECTRIC COOPERATIVES IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT MEMBERSHIP ORGANIZATION WHOSE MEMBERS HAVE VOTING RIGHTS.
ALL BOARD MEMBERS ARE CHOSEN BY THE ASSOCIATION MEMBERS.
THE BOARD MEMBERS OF THE ASSOCIATION OF ILLINOIS ELECTRIC COOPERATIVES REVIEW THE FORM 990 PRIOR TO IT BEING FILED.
THE BOARD MONITORS AND ENFORCES COMPLIANCE WITH THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY THROUGH AN ANNUAL WRITTEN DISCLOSURE.

THE COMPENSATION FOR THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER IS DETERMINED BY THE BOARD'S COMPENSATION COMMITTEE. THE COMMITTEE COMPARES THE COMPENSATION AMOUNT WITH COMPARABLE SALARY DATA FOR SIMILAR STATE ASSOCIATION CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICERS.
THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT PUBLISH THEIR GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, ETC. FOR THE PUBLIC; HOWEVER, THEY ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
